body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for reaching out to us. My name is Russell Clark and I represent AutoZone, your trusted car dealership. May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Julie. Before we proceed, for security purposes, could you please provide me with the last two digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, the last two digits are seven five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Julie. Additionally, can you confirm the total number of vehicles you currently own?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Julie. If you don't mind me asking, could you please provide your email address for further communication?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that, Julie. Your privacy is our utmost priority. We appreciate your cooperation. Is there anything else you'd like to discuss today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all. Thank you for your assistance.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Julie. Thank you for your time. Should you have any further questions, feel free to reach out to us. Have a great day!
